{
  "stem": "10119.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 85.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they didn't last very long, maybe for about a year or so.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then Hungary came-- came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were right in the middle of war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Between the siege and Hungary, we were just out of school for a year.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I missed out an awful lot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we-- we had other land, and we worked in the land.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we helped around the house, nothing special.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We tried to study as much as we could.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The young-- the men, all the Hebrew teachers, were taken away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They brought in a young student, a yeshiva [? bocher ?] to teach the boys, but he would not-- would not teach the girls.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So whatever I learned in Hebrew, my mother used to sit with me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When everyone went to bed, she was sitting and teaching me how to read and how to write.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a very tough time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A public school, public school, Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we switched to-- to Hungarian when Hungary came over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I must have been in the fifth grade, they took over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we lost about a year.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went into school.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We did not speak a word of English, and the teachers did not speak a-- a word of Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we studied.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We tried to understand, which I learned the language at least.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This is a plus.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A little bit of Czech and Hungarian--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--we learned.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, I [? started off with Yiddish ?], which was normal.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the home-- in the house we spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Outside we spoke Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So right away, we-- we had two languages to start with.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I was by my aunt's-- in-- in my aunt's house, I still had one year of school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To go.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I went from there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then it-- the war got to be too close.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pesel, Pesel Berkovich.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And his name was Simon Laizer, and her name was Pesel Berkovich.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was still the same town, the same school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a small town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We only had like two schools.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there was no problem going to school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The pograms already had started.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from what we knew about it is they might come into one part of the town and take it one day.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then the next day, or the next month, whenever they decided, they came to the other town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we always had anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I didn't understand when they used to tell it-- [UKRAINIAN].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's in Ukrainian-- Jew go to-- to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I was a kid, and we didn't know about it, not enough.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The friends we were playing with.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had friends.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we had-- we-- we grew-- I grew up in a mixed-- mixed people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Jews had most of the-- all the stores.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had land.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had-- it was a very rich community.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The people there owned a lot of land.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, not-- not the Jewish people, but the gentiles.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we worked with them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Like, in the springtime, my father could go and buy up-- after the blooming, buy up some fruit.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then, of course, in the fall we shipped it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The same thing when the-- with sending away some sheep.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They used to call us [NON-ENGLISH], which in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We rented the sheep, and we hired a shepherd.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the shepherds, they made cheese.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So by the end of the-- the end of the [INAUDIBLE], in the fall, we had a cheese to sell, which was [? extra. ?] It was part of a business.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The cheeses?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, ?] they were just-- they were-- they were-- they sold it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, we didn't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But some of the cheeses don't require refrigeration.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in the fall it was already cold.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then they came back, maybe they had-- they had the cheese done.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe there were refrigerators, not as far as I remember.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To keep something fresh, my grandfather had a big basement.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was funny, because there was a little water running through it, a little brook.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So if he had something extra, we always put it in my grandfather's basement.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we didn't have any.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We put-- we had everything fresh.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were fresh produce, fresh milk, fresh things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The wintertime we saved the fruits from the summer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't know if you ever heard of it, they used to put away the potatoes, the beets, outside.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was put in underground and covered it up with the ground.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you took it out-- in the winter you opened up, and you took it out, and it was fine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, that helped me to survive in the camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
